        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} to finally get your feet into the water. In Dauin there is a nature conservation reserve that includes large parts of the coastal waters because there is a coral reef that should reach the beach. </p>
        <p> I only sat in the cafe for 2 hours and worked a little.
            I then let myself be explained to the beach and made my way. After 5 minutes by walking through rough terrain, the beach came into sight.
            The sand has a beautiful milk coffee brown and is relatively coarse -grained.
            I didn't expect that because the beach on a coral reef is usually white and consists of dead corals. </p>
        <p> But not here. The best thing was that I was almost completely alone on the beach. I only ran about 100m along the beach before some small bamboo pavilions invited me to linger. I made it comfortable there and decided to work through another task. I still had battery. So I imagine work in paradise and yes it was really paradise. </p>

